Epoch:0 | TOPIC | Scientist1:The proposed **Attention Residual Gaussian Distribution (ARGD)** module enhances VAE-based sign language translation by integrating attention-driven residual signals into the posterior inference process. This allows semantically critical text elements to dynamically modulate the latent Gaussian distribution’s parameters, improving fine-grained semantic grounding—especially for non-manual markers—and promoting better latent disentanglement. The approach also increases robustness to noisy text encodings in low-resource settings. Evaluation is planned using both automated metrics (e.g., BLEU, FID) and human assessments of grammatical accuracy, with ablation studies to isolate ARGD's impact. A hierarchical extension is suggested for future work. The team is asked to consider piloting ARGD on the PHOENIX14T dataset before scaling up.
