Furthermore, the idea of creating a “semantic corridor” in the latent space via a GNN-encoded AMR prior manifold introduces a novel form of inductive bias that goes beyond simple multi-task learning or feature sharing. This represents a paradigm shift—from feed-forward semantic integration to feedback-driven semantic steering—which is not explored in any of the referenced works.

